Menu="Utilities"
Title="CI Runner Farm"
Icon="icon-docker"
Tag="server"
---
<?php
/* CI Runner Farm settings page - native Unraid markdown form + inline help */
$plugin   = 'ci-runner-farm';
$cfgfile  = "/boot/config/plugins/$plugin/config.cfg";
$cfg      = file_exists($cfgfile) ? parse_ini_file($cfgfile) : [];
$has_token= file_exists("/boot/config/plugins/$plugin/token");
$csrf     = $var['csrf_token'] ?? '';
$patScope = (($cfg['GH_SCOPE'] ?? 'repo') === 'org') ? 'repo,admin:org' : 'repo';
$patUrl   = 'https://github.com/settings/tokens/new?description=Unraid+CI+Runner+Farm&scopes='.$patScope;
$dfFile   = "/boot/config/plugins/$plugin/Dockerfile";
if (!is_file($dfFile)) $dfFile = "/usr/local/emhttp/plugins/$plugin/default.Dockerfile";
$dockerfile = is_file($dfFile) ? file_get_contents($dfFile) : '';
if (!function_exists('crf_g'))   { function crf_g($cfg,$k,$d=''){ return htmlspecialchars($cfg[$k] ?? $d, ENT_QUOTES); } }
if (!function_exists('crf_sel')) { function crf_sel($cfg,$k,$val,$d){ return (($cfg[$k] ?? $d) === $val) ? 'selected' : ''; } }
?>
<link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="<?autov('/webGui/styles/jquery.filetree.css')?>">
<script src="<?autov('/webGui/javascript/jquery.filetree.js')?>" charset="utf-8"></script>

<form markdown="1" name="ci_runner_farm" method="POST" action="/update.php" target="progressFrame">
<input type="hidden" name="#file" value="ci-runner-farm/config.cfg">

_(GitHub scope)_:
: <select name="GH_SCOPE">
  <option value="repo" <?=crf_sel($cfg,'GH_SCOPE','repo','repo')?>>repo (per-repository)</option>
  <option value="org" <?=crf_sel($cfg,'GH_SCOPE','org','repo')?>>org (organization-wide)</option>
  </select>

:crf_scope_plug:
> repo = register runners on specific repositories.
>
> org = one shared pool available to every repo in the org (recommended when you have more than one repo).
:end

_(Org owner)_:
: <input type="text" name="GH_OWNER" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'GH_OWNER','unraid')?>">

:crf_owner_plug:
> GitHub organization name. Used only when scope is org (e.g. unraid).
:end

_(Target repos)_:
: <input type="text" name="GH_REPOS" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'GH_REPOS','unraid/repo-a unraid/repo-b')?>">

:crf_repos_plug:
> Space-separated owner/repo list, used when scope is repo. Runners are spread across these repos round-robin.
:end

_(Runner group)_:
: <input type="text" name="RUNNER_GROUP" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'RUNNER_GROUP')?>">

:crf_group_plug:
> Optional runner group (org scope) to restrict which repos may use the pool — e.g. exclude public repos so fork PRs never run here.
:end

_(Concurrent runners)_:
: <input type="number" name="RUNNER_COUNT" min="1" max="20" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'RUNNER_COUNT','4')?>">

:crf_count_plug:
> How many runner containers to launch. Each runs one job at a time, so this equals your maximum number of concurrent builds.
:end

_(Runner labels)_:
: <input type="text" name="RUNNER_LABELS" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'RUNNER_LABELS','self-hosted,unraid,build')?>">

:crf_labels_plug:
> Comma-separated labels that workflows target with runs-on, e.g. self-hosted,unraid,build.
:end

_(CPUs per runner)_:
: <input type="text" name="RUNNER_CPUS" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'RUNNER_CPUS','')?>" placeholder="blank = uncapped">

:crf_cpus_plug:
> Hard CPU cap per runner. Leave blank for uncapped — the Linux scheduler time-shares CPU fairly across all runners, so a lone build can use the whole box.
:end

_(Memory per runner)_:
: <input type="text" name="RUNNER_MEMORY" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'RUNNER_MEMORY','16g')?>">

:crf_mem_plug:
> Hard memory cap per runner, e.g. 16g. Kept capped because memory is not time-shared like CPU — an uncapped leak could OOM the host or the other workloads.
:end

_(Cache root)_:
: <input type="text" id="CACHE_ROOT" name="CACHE_ROOT" autocomplete="off" spellcheck="false" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'CACHE_ROOT','/mnt/github-runner')?>" data-pickroot="/mnt" data-pickfolders="true" data-pickfilter="HIDE_FILES_FILTER" placeholder="/mnt/github-runner">

:crf_cache_plug:
> Pool path for warm shared caches (pnpm/npm/yarn) and, if tmpfs is off, the bind workspaces. Click the field to browse and pick a folder. Use a fast pool — default is the github-runner pool.
:end

_(Workspace tmpfs size)_:
: <input type="text" name="WORK_TMPFS_SIZE" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'WORK_TMPFS_SIZE','8g')?>" placeholder="blank = bind to pool">

:crf_tmpfs_plug:
> Size of the RAM-backed per-job workspace, e.g. 8g — a clean, fast workspace each job while caches stay warm. Blank binds the workspace to the pool instead of RAM.
:end

_(Runner image)_:
: <input type="text" name="IMAGE" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'IMAGE','myoung34/github-runner:latest')?>">

:crf_image_plug:
> Docker image used for each runner. Default: myoung34/github-runner:latest.
:end

_(Ephemeral)_:
: <select name="EPHEMERAL">
  <option value="false" <?=crf_sel($cfg,'EPHEMERAL','false','false')?>>false (persistent, warm cache)</option>
  <option value="true" <?=crf_sel($cfg,'EPHEMERAL','true','false')?>>true (clean per job)</option>
  </select>

:crf_ephemeral_plug:
> false = persistent runner, package caches stay warm between jobs. true = fresh runner re-registered per job (cleanest state, slightly slower first run).
:end

_(Docker-in-docker mode)_:
: <select name="DIND">
  <option value="true" <?=crf_sel($cfg,'DIND','true','true')?>>true (own daemon per runner, privileged)</option>
  <option value="false" <?=crf_sel($cfg,'DIND','false','true')?>>false (use host docker.sock)</option>
  </select>

:crf_dind_plug:
> Docker-in-docker: each runner runs its own Docker daemon (requires --privileged).
>
> Fixes GitHub Actions services: networking (localhost:port becomes reachable from job steps) and "port already allocated" collisions between parallel jobs. Recommended when workflows use services: or service containers.
:end

_(Share host docker.sock)_:
: <select name="SHARE_DOCKER_SOCK">
  <option value="true" <?=crf_sel($cfg,'SHARE_DOCKER_SOCK','true','true')?>>true</option>
  <option value="false" <?=crf_sel($cfg,'SHARE_DOCKER_SOCK','false','true')?>>false</option>
  </select>

:crf_sock_plug:
> Mount the host Docker socket so jobs can start service containers (e.g. postgres for integration tests). PRIVATE repos only — never expose this to public/fork-PR code (root-equivalent host access).
:end

_(Autoscaling)_:
: <select name="AUTOSCALE">
  <option value="false" <?=crf_sel($cfg,'AUTOSCALE','false','false')?>>off (fixed at Concurrent runners)</option>
  <option value="true" <?=crf_sel($cfg,'AUTOSCALE','true','false')?>>on (fleet floats by demand)</option>
  </select>

:crf_autoscale_plug:
> When on, a daemon grows/shrinks the fleet by demand instead of using a fixed count. It keeps a warm idle buffer: when idle runners drop below the buffer (jobs are consuming them) it adds runners; when too many sit idle it removes them. Bounded by Min/Max, with grace to avoid flapping. Only ever removes idle runners, never a runner mid-job.
:end

_(Autoscale: min runners)_:
: <input type="number" name="AUTOSCALE_MIN" min="0" max="40" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'AUTOSCALE_MIN','2')?>">

:crf_asmin_plug:
> The floor — the fleet never drops below this, even fully idle. Keeps a couple warm so the first jobs never wait.
:end

_(Autoscale: max runners)_:
: <input type="number" name="AUTOSCALE_MAX" min="1" max="40" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'AUTOSCALE_MAX','16')?>">

:crf_asmax_plug:
> The ceiling — the fleet never grows past this. Set it to the most the box can run alongside the other workloads (the host: ~16 leaves CPU/RAM headroom).
:end

_(Autoscale: warm idle buffer)_:
: <input type="number" name="AUTOSCALE_MIN_IDLE" min="1" max="20" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'AUTOSCALE_MIN_IDLE','2')?>">

:crf_asbuf_plug:
> Keep at least this many idle runners ready. When idle drops below it, scale up — so a burst of jobs finds warm runners instead of queueing. Higher = more headroom but more idle containers.
:end

_(Autoscale: step)_:
: <input type="number" name="AUTOSCALE_STEP" min="1" max="10" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'AUTOSCALE_STEP','2')?>">

:crf_asstep_plug:
> How many runners to add or remove per adjustment.
:end

_(Autoscale: check interval (s))_:
: <input type="number" name="AUTOSCALE_INTERVAL" min="10" max="600" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'AUTOSCALE_INTERVAL','30')?>">

:crf_asint_plug:
> Seconds between demand checks. Lower = more responsive, more churn.
:end

_(Autoscale: scale-down grace)_:
: <input type="number" name="AUTOSCALE_IDLE_GRACE" min="1" max="60" value="<?=crf_g($cfg,'AUTOSCALE_IDLE_GRACE','5')?>">

:crf_asgrace_plug:
> How many consecutive over-idle checks before removing runners. Scale-up is immediate; scale-down waits this long to avoid flapping during brief lulls.
:end

&nbsp;
: <input type="submit" name="Apply" value="_(Apply)_">

</form>

<hr>
<div>
<p><strong>GitHub token (PAT)</strong> &nbsp;<a href="<?=$patUrl?>" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Create a pre-scoped PAT on GitHub &#8599;</a><br>
Stored at <code>/boot/config/plugins/ci-runner-farm/token</code> (chmod 600), never in config.cfg.
Status: <strong id="crf-tok"><?= $has_token ? 'configured &#10004;' : 'not set' ?></strong></p>
<p>
  <input type="password" id="crf-token" placeholder="ghp_... (scopes pre-filled by the link)" style="width:28em">
  <input type="button" value="Save token" onclick="crfSetToken()">
  <input type="button" value="Clear" onclick="crfAction('clear-token')">
</p>

<hr>
<p><strong>Fleet control</strong></p>
<p>
  <input type="button" value="Start" onclick="crfAction('start')">
  <input type="button" value="Stop" onclick="crfAction('stop')">
  <input type="button" value="Restart" onclick="crfAction('restart')">
  <input type="button" value="Validate (no token)" onclick="crfAction('validate')">
  &nbsp; Scale to <input type="number" id="crf-n" min="0" max="20" value="4" style="width:4em">
  <input type="button" value="Scale" onclick="crfScale()">
</p>

<table class="crf-status" id="crf-table" style="text-align:left">
  <thead><tr><th>Runner</th><th>State</th><th>Phase</th><th>CPU</th><th>Mem</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody><tr><td colspan="5">loading...</td></tr></tbody>
</table>
<div id="crf-log" style="white-space:pre-wrap;font-family:monospace;font-size:12px;max-height:220px;overflow:auto;background:#1e1e1e;color:#ddd;padding:8px;border-radius:4px;margin-top:8px"></div>

<hr>
<p><strong>Runner image builder</strong> &mdash; edit the Dockerfile for the runner image (add apt packages, tools, browsers), Save, then Build. It's tagged as the configured image (<code><?=crf_g($cfg,'IMAGE','ci-runner-farm-runner:latest')?></code>); restart the fleet to use a new build. Build output streams to the log above.</p>
<textarea id="crf-dockerfile" rows="14" spellcheck="false" style="width:100%;font-family:monospace;font-size:12px"><?=htmlspecialchars($dockerfile, ENT_QUOTES)?></textarea>
<p>
  <input type="button" value="Save Dockerfile" onclick="crfSaveDf()">
  <input type="button" value="Build image" onclick="crfBuild()">
  <span id="crf-build-status" style="color:#888"></span>
</p>
</div>

<style>
  .crf-status td,.crf-status th{padding:4px 10px}
  .crf-pill{padding:1px 8px;border-radius:10px;font-size:11px;color:#fff}
  .crf-idle{background:#3a7}.crf-busy{background:#c84}.crf-error{background:#c44}
  .crf-starting{background:#789}.crf-exited{background:#888}
</style>

<script>
const CRF_CSRF = "<?=$csrf?>";
const CRF_URL  = "/plugins/ci-runner-farm/include/exec.php";
function crfPost(p){
  p.csrf_token = CRF_CSRF;
  return fetch(CRF_URL,{method:'POST',headers:{'Content-Type':'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'},
    body:Object.entries(p).map(([k,v])=>encodeURIComponent(k)+'='+encodeURIComponent(v)).join('&')}).then(r=>r.json());
}
function crfLog(o){ document.getElementById('crf-log').textContent = (o.log||JSON.stringify(o)); }
function crfAction(a){ crfPost({action:a}).then(o=>{crfLog(o); crfRefresh();}); }
function crfScale(){ crfPost({action:'scale',n:document.getElementById('crf-n').value}).then(o=>{crfLog(o); crfRefresh();}); }
function crfSetToken(){ const t=document.getElementById('crf-token').value; if(!t)return;
  crfPost({action:'set-token',token:t}).then(o=>{document.getElementById('crf-tok').innerHTML=o.ok?'configured &#10004;':'error';document.getElementById('crf-token').value='';}); }
function crfRefresh(){
  crfPost({action:'status-json'}).then(d=>{
    const tb=document.querySelector('#crf-table tbody'); tb.innerHTML='';
    if(!d.runners||!d.runners.length){ tb.innerHTML='<tr><td colspan="5">no managed runners (configured: '+(d.configured||0)+')</td></tr>'; return; }
    d.runners.forEach(r=>{ const cls=r.state!=='running'?'crf-exited':('crf-'+r.phase);
      tb.innerHTML+='<tr><td>'+r.name+'</td><td>'+r.state+'</td><td><span class="crf-pill '+cls+'">'+r.phase+'</span></td><td>'+(r.cpus?r.cpus+'c':'max')+'</td><td>'+r.mem_gb+'g</td></tr>'; });
  }).catch(()=>{});
}
crfRefresh(); setInterval(crfRefresh,5000);
function crfSaveDf(cb){ crfPost({action:'save-dockerfile',dockerfile:document.getElementById('crf-dockerfile').value}).then(o=>{ document.getElementById('crf-build-status').textContent = o.ok?'saved':('error: '+(o.error||'')); if(typeof cb==='function') cb(); }); }
function crfBuild(){ document.getElementById('crf-build-status').textContent='saving + building...'; crfSaveDf(function(){ crfPost({action:'build-image'}).then(()=>crfPollBuild()); }); }
function crfPollBuild(){ crfPost({action:'build-log'}).then(d=>{ document.getElementById('crf-log').textContent=d.log||''; if(d.running){ document.getElementById('crf-build-status').textContent='building...'; setTimeout(crfPollBuild,2000);} else { document.getElementById('crf-build-status').textContent='build finished — restart the fleet to use it'; } }); }
// Native Unraid folder picker on the Cache root path field
if (window.jQuery) jQuery(function($){ if ($.fn.fileTreeAttach) $("#CACHE_ROOT").fileTreeAttach(); });
</script>
